. . . One. "Oh, this senseless life of ours!" thought Nicholas. "All this misery, and money, and D61okhov, and anger, and honor it's all nonsense . . . but this is real. . . . Now then, Natdsha, now then, dearest! Now then, darling! How will she take that si? She's taken it! Thank God!" And without noticing that he was singing, to strengthen the si he sung a second, a third below the high note. "Ah, God! How fine! Did I really take it? How fortunate!" he thought.
